                  <persName id="t17870912-14-person169">
                  JANE
                   DOLMAN
               <interp inst="t17870912-14-person169" type="surname" value="DOLMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870912-14-person169" type="given" value="JANE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870912-14-person169" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I took the clothes out of the prisoner's lap in my master Mr. Jayes's yard; it was on the 16th of July; between three and four in the afternoon, the linen was hanging on the lines in the yard to dry, and had been there sometime; I was in the kitchen, washing, and the door was open, and I saw him coming from the yard with these things in his lap; the passage faces the kitchen door; I took hold of his coat, and bid him stop, and followed him into the kitchen, and took the clothes from his lap, and throwed them down on the kitchen stones.</p>
               <p>(The property produced, and proved by the witness.)</p>
